  "text": "The respondent is comparing a time when people grew one crop of rainfed wheat, for which there was sufficient soil moisture. Presently, farmers take two crops a year, driving up water requirements. However, this is not factored into perceptions of decreased water availability. Thus, farmers may attribute water scarcity to declining rainfall when it may be because of increasing water demand due to increased cultivation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
